## Setup

Initialize the project environment:

```bash
just init
```

This will:
- Fetch all dependencies via `mix deps.get`
- Compile the project via `mix compile`

## Usage

Run the main application:

```bash
just run
```

See all available commands:

```bash
just help
```

## Development

### Available Commands

- `just init` - Initialize development environment
- `just run` - Run the main application
- `just destroy` - Remove build artifacts and dependencies
- `just help` - Show available commands

### Code Quality

- `just code-style` - Check code formatting (read-only)
- `just code-format` - Auto-format code
- `just code-lint` - Run Credo static analysis (strict)
- `just code-typecheck` - Run Dialyzer type checking
- `just code-security` - Run Sobelow security scan
- `just code-spell` - Check spelling
- `just code-audit` - Scan for dependency vulnerabilities

### Testing

- `just test` - Run tests with coverage ({{coverage_threshold}}% threshold)

### CI

- `just ci` - Run all validation checks (verbose)
- `just ci-quiet` - Run all checks (silent, fail-fast)

The CI pipeline runs the following steps in order:
1. `init` - Initialize environment
2. `code-format` - Auto-format code
3. `code-style` - Verify formatting
4. `code-lint` - Credo static analysis
5. `code-typecheck` - Dialyzer type checking
6. `code-security` - Sobelow security scan
7. `code-spell` - Spell checking
8. `code-audit` - Dependency vulnerability scanning
9. `test` - Unit tests with coverage

